## Proposal
                      
### Please re-state the problem that we are trying to solve in this issue.
- Web - Bank Account - User is signed out when clicking 'Update to USD'
### What is the root cause of that problem?
- After entering an Email and clicking on button "Join" in OD, it will redirect user to the ND.
- In ND, go to setting => profile => contact-method => contact-method/detail, then enter the magic code, the session has expired (In essence, it validates the email, so the old authToken of the login passwordless method without email verification will be invalidated. But the user is not signed-out). 
- Then, if any API is called, the error "Your session has expired. Please sign in again." is returned from BE side. Now, user is navigated to sign-in screen
### What changes do you think we should make in order to solve the problem?
- We need to sign-out right after the API ValidateSecondaryLogin is called by creating the variable ```shouldSignOut``` in [here](https://github.com/Expensify/App/blob/main/src/pages/settings/Profile/Contacts/ContactMethodDetailsPage.js):
```
const shouldSignOut = isDefaultContactMethod && !loginData.validatedDate && !isFailedAddContactMethod
```
- And then updating:
https://github.com/Expensify/App/blob/d985a0ee2604686911f34c99f5298af059622244/src/pages/settings/Profile/Contacts/ContactMethodDetailsPage.js#L121-L130
to:
````diff
    componentDidUpdate(prevProps) {
        const validatedDate = lodashGet(this.props.loginList, [this.getContactMethod(), 'validatedDate']);
        const prevValidatedDate = lodashGet(prevProps.loginList, [this.getContactMethod(), 'validatedDate']);

        // Navigate to methods page on successful magic code verification
        // validatedDate property is responsible to decide the status of the magic code verification
+        if(shouldSignOut){
+            // Sign out logic here
+            Session.signOutAndRedirectToSignIn();
+            return
+        }
        if (!prevValidatedDate && validatedDate) {
            Navigation.goBack(ROUTES.SETTINGS_CONTACT_METHODS.route);
        }
    }
````

### What alternative solutions did you explore? (Optional)
- Also, when API ValidateSecondaryLogin is called, beside the ```loginList``` data, BE should return new authToken, credentials to update to Onyx and then, we can update the app to make sure it works properly, for example, authenticatePusher. So, with this solution, the user do not need to signe out. 
- First, create a variable ```shouldUpdateSession``` in [here](https://github.com/Expensify/App/blob/main/src/pages/settings/Profile/Contacts/ContactMethodDetailsPage.js)
```
const shouldUpdateSession = isDefaultContactMethod && !loginData.validatedDate && !isFailedAddContactMethod
```
- And then updating:
https://github.com/Expensify/App/blob/d985a0ee2604686911f34c99f5298af059622244/src/pages/settings/Profile/Contacts/ContactMethodDetailsPage.js#L121-L130
to:
````diff
    componentDidUpdate(prevProps) {
        const validatedDate = lodashGet(this.props.loginList, [this.getContactMethod(), 'validatedDate']);
        const prevValidatedDate = lodashGet(prevProps.loginList, [this.getContactMethod(), 'validatedDate']);

        // Navigate to methods page on successful magic code verification
        // validatedDate property is responsible to decide the status of the magic code verification
+        if(shouldUpdateSession){
+            // Update session logic here
+  PusherConnectionManager.init();
+        Pusher.init({
+            appKey: CONFIG.PUSHER.APP_KEY,
+            cluster: CONFIG.PUSHER.CLUSTER,
+            authEndpoint: `${CONFIG.EXPENSIFY.DEFAULT_API_ROOT}api?command=AuthenticatePusher`,
+        }).then(() => {
+            User.subscribeToUserEvents();
+        });
+            return
+        }
        if (!prevValidatedDate && validatedDate) {
            Navigation.goBack(ROUTES.SETTINGS_CONTACT_METHODS.route); 
        }
    }
````
